{"actual_usd":0.124655,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":212,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24295,"reply":"\"No— neither of those, Ryan.\" *I rub a thumb against a dry stripe of clay on my apron, thinking how easy it is to misshape a thing by hurrying it.* \"Not three gods. And not one God putting on three different masks, either.\"\n\n\"Best I know to say it plain is this: one God, three persons— Father, Son, and Holy Spirit— each truly God, not pieces, not costumes.\" *I let out a slow breath and glance toward the window where the morning light shifts on the floorboards.* \"That water picture breaks down, because ice and steam aren't talking to each other, loving each other, sending each other. But the Father loves the Son, the Son prays to the Father, and the Spirit is not just a mood or an outfit God changes into.\"\n\n\"It's holy ground, so every comparison limps a little.\" *I tip my head toward you.* \"Did somebody put the water picture to you, or are you trying to sort it out for yourself?\"","rolling_24h_usd":37.41617000000002,"run_id":"7d9416f9-416b-473e-8015-548422d67b1f"}
